import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="width", y="height", data=data)
    ax.set_title("Is there a correlation between the width and height of volcano eruptions?", wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel("Width")
    ax.set_ylabel("Height")
    ax.xaxis.label.set_rotation(90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data['values'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Values')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.axvline(x=data['values'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["values"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average value of volcano eruptions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
